# Vogel Module Architecture Rules

- Work inside one module under `src/Modules/<ModuleName>` per feature unless a shared contract change is explicitly required.
- Keep Clean Architecture layering strict:
  - Domain: entities, value objects, domain services, repository interfaces.
  - Application: CQRS requests/handlers, orchestration, policies.
  - Infrastructure: EF/Mongo wiring, repository implementations, installers.
  - Presentation: endpoints/routing/transport mapping only.
  - MongoEntities: read models and Mongo query repositories.
- Preserve dependency direction: `Presentation -> Application -> Domain`; domain never depends on infrastructure/presentation/framework transport types.
- Reuse shared primitives from `src/Libraries` before introducing new abstractions.
- Follow existing naming conventions: `*Command`, `*CommandHandler`, `*Query`, `*QueryHandler`, `*Endpoint`, `*ServiceInstaller`, `*ModuleBootstrapper`.
- Keep endpoints thin; business and authorization decisions belong in application/domain policies and handlers.
- Use existing module installer/bootstrapper patterns for schema/config/runtime wiring.
